{"title_page": "Peppermint extract", "text_new": "'''Peppermint extract''' is an [[herbal extract]] of [[peppermint]] (''Mentha \u00d7 piperita'') made from the [[essential oils]] of peppermint leaves. [[Peppermint]] is a hybrid of [[Mentha aquatica|water mint]] and [[spearmint]]<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://nccih.nih.gov/health/peppermintoil|title=Peppermint|last=National Center for Complementary and Integrative Health.|first=|date=2016|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=4 February 2020}}</ref> and was indigenous to Europe and the Middle East before it became common in other regions, such as North America and Asia.\n\nPeppermint is commonly used in [[cooking]], as a [[dietary supplement]], as an herbal or [[alternative medicine]], as a pest repellent,<ref name=\":0\" /> and a flavor or fragrance agent for cleaning products, cosmetics, mouthwash, chewing gum, and candies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com.ph/books?id=AVsARRPzvrgC&printsec=frontcover&dq=peppermint+oil&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwji2rCu37bnAhV3yYsBHUAZCYcQ6AEIKDAA#v=onepage&q=peppermint%20oil&f=false|title=Peppermint oil: Synopsis of information|publisher=United States Bureau of Foreign and Domestic Commerce |date=1949|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=4 February 2020}}</ref> Its active ingredients, such as menthol, menthone, and menthyl acetate, give it its minty properties that result in a fresh and cooling sensation when used. Moreover, peppermint is also a good source of vitamin A, vitamin C, magnesium, and potassium.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.encyclopedia.com/plants-and-animals/plants/plants/peppermint |title=Peppermint |date=2020 |publisher=[]Encyclopedia.com]] |url-status=live |archive-url= |archive-date= |access-date=4 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n== History and Extraction ==\nPeppermint and peppermint oil have been used for thousands of years in Ancient Egypt, Greece, and Rome<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.aromafoundry.com/blogs/aroma-foundry/peppermint-oil-uses-description-recipes-precautions|title=Peppermint Oil: Uses, Benefits, & More|last=Santos|first=F.|date=2020|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=4 February 2020}}</ref>. Historical records reveal the use of peppermint in Egyptian tombs and pyramids<ref name=\":1\" />. However, it was not until Carolus Linnaeus catalogued the plant in 1753 that the very first documentation of the plant\u2019s characteristics was written.\n\nPeppermint extract can be obtained through various means, the most common being steam distillation, solvent extraction, and soxhelet extraction<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Siddeeg|first=A.|last2=Mukhtar|first2=R.M.E.|last3=Salih|first3=Z.A.|last4=Ali|first4=A.O.|date=2018|title=Extraction and characterization of peppermint (Mentha piperita) essential oil and its assessment as antioxidant and antibacterial|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/328631741_Extraction_and_Characterization_of_Peppermint_Mentha_piperita_Essential_Oil_and_its_Assessment_as_Antioxidant_and_Antibacterial|journal=|volume=|pages=|via=ResearchGate}}</ref>.\n\n== Uses ==\nPeppermint extract is commonly used as an antiseptic, anti-viral, stimulant, and a flavoring agent<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Tanu|first=B.|last2=Harpreet|first2=K.|date=2016|title=Benefits of essential oil|url=https://mafiadoc.com/benefits-of-essential-oil-journal-of-chemical-and-pharmaceutical_5c174b1f097c47d4198b473d.html|journal=Journal of Chemical and Pharmaceutical Research|volume=8(6)|pages=143-149|via=}}</ref>. Moderate levels of it can be safely mixed into food items, or it can also be applied topically, sprayed on surfaces as a household cleaner, or inhaled using aromatherapy<ref name=\":2\" />.\n\n===Uses in cooking===\n{{unreferenced section|date=February 2015}}\nPeppermint extract can be used to add a peppermint flavor to [[baked goods]], [[desserts]], and [[candy]], particularly [[candy canes]], [[mint (candy)|mints]], and peppermint patties. Extracts for cooking may be labeled as pure, natural, imitation, or artificial. While pure and natural extracts contain peppermint oil specifically, imitation and artificial extracts generally use a mix of ingredients to achieve a flavor resembling peppermint.\n\nPeppermint extract can be substituted in [[recipes]] with peppermint oil (a stronger ingredient primarily used in candy-making), [[cr\u00e8me de menthe]], or [[schnapps|peppermint schnapps]]. If the food is not heated, the alcoholic properties of [[liqueurs]] may remain present in the finished product.\n\nPeppermint extract may also be added to hot water to create [[peppermint tea]].\n\n=== Medicinal uses ===\nMedicinal uses of peppermint extract are well-documented, however the efficacy of most applications is only beginning to be tested in clinical trials.\n\nPeppermint extract is commonly used to soothe symptoms of the [[common cold]] and the [[flu]], and as a [[digestion|digestive]] aid to relieve [[bloating]] and [[flatulence]]. It is an [[anti-inflammatory]] which be used to treat [[arthritis]] and [[rheumatism]].<ref name=\"oils\">{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/completebookofes00worw/page/1|title=The complete book of essential oils and aromatherapy|last=Worwood|first=V.A.|publisher=New World Library|year=1991|isbn=0-931432-82-0|location=|pages=[https://archive.org/details/completebookofes00worw/page/1 1, 20]|url-access=registration}}</ref> It may be used to aid in the relief of pain from [[menstrual cramp]]s and [[headache]]s.<ref name=oils/><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Heshmati|first1=A.|last2=Dolatian|first2=M.|last3=Mojab|first3=F.|last4=Shakeri|first4=N.|last5=Nikkhah|first5=S.|last6=Mahmoodi|first6=Z.|date=2016|year=|title=The effect of peppermint (Mentha piperita) capsules on the severity of primary dysmenorrhea|url=|journal=Journal of Herbal Medicine|volume=6|issue=3|pages=137\u2013141|doi=10.1016/j.hermed.2016.05.001|via=}}</ref> Additionally, peppermint oil may be an effective remedy for [[irritable bowel syndrome]] with constipation.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Ford|first1=A.C.|last2=Talley|first2=N.J.|last3=Spiegel|first3=B.M.R.|last4=Foxx-Orenstein|first4=A.E.|last5=Schiller|first5=L.|last6=Quigley|first6=E.M.M.|last7=Moayyedi|first7=P.|date=|year=2008|title=Effect of fibre, antispasmodics, and peppermint oil in the treatment of irritable bowel syndrome: Systematic review and meta-analysis|url=|journal=BMJ|volume=337|pages=a2313|doi=10.1136/bmj.a2313|pmc=2583392|pmid=19008265|via=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Cappello|first1=G.|last2=Coraggio|first2=D.|last3=De Berardinis|first3=G.|last4=Spezzaferro|first4=M.|last5=Grossi|first5=L.|last6=Marzio|first6=L.|date=|year=2006|title=Peppermint oil (Mintoil\u00ae) in the treatment of irritable bowel syndrome. A prospective double blind placebo controlled randomized trial|url=|journal=Digestive and Liver Disease|volume=38|pages=S202|doi=10.1016/S1590-8658(06)80548-7|via=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Grigoleit|first1=H.|last2=Grigoleit|first2=P.|date=|year=2005|title=Peppermint oil in irritable bowel syndrome|url=|journal=Phytomedicine|volume=12|issue=8|pages=601\u2013606|doi=10.1016/j.phymed.2004.10.005|via=}}</ref> It is also used as a natural remedy for [[toothache]].<ref name=oils/>\n\n===Use as a pest repellent===\nPeppermint oil is commonly used to repel ants, flying insects, rodents, and spiders. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gardenguides.com/81346-use-peppermint-oil-pest-control.html|title=How to use peppermint oil for pest control|last=Douglas|first=E.|date=2017|website=GardenGuides.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n===Use as a physical performance enhancer===\nPeppermint oil is used in endurance sports to improve mental and physical stamina.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Meamarbashi|first1=A.|date=|year=2014|title=Instant effects of peppermint essential oil on the physiological parameters and exercise performance|url=|journal=Avicenna Journal of Phytomedicine|volume=4|issue=1|pages=72\u20138|pmc=4103722|pmid=25050303|via=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Meamarbashi|first1=A.|last2=Rajabi|first2=A.|date=|year=2013|title=The effects of peppermint on exercise performance|url=|journal=Journal of the International Society of Sports Nutrition|volume=10|issue=1|pages=15|doi=10.1186/1550-2783-10-15|pmc=3607906|pmid=23517650|via=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Food additives]]\n", "text_old": "'''Peppermint extract''' is an [[herbal extract]] of [[peppermint]] (''Mentha \u00d7 piperita'') made from the [[essential oils]] of peppermint leaves. [[Peppermint]] is a hybrid of water mint and spearmint<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://nccih.nih.gov/health/peppermintoil|title=Peppermint|last=National Center for Complementary and Integrative Health.|first=|date=2016|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=4 February 2020}}</ref> and was indigenous to Europe and the Middle East before it became common in other regions, such as North America and Asia.\n\nPeppermint is commonly used in [[cooking]], as a [[dietary supplement]], as an herbal or [[alternative medicine]], as a pest repellent,<ref name=\":0\" /> and a flavor or fragrance agent for cleaning products, cosmetics, mouthwash, chewing gum, and candies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com.ph/books?id=AVsARRPzvrgC&printsec=frontcover&dq=peppermint+oil&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwji2rCu37bnAhV3yYsBHUAZCYcQ6AEIKDAA#v=onepage&q=peppermint%20oil&f=false|title=Peppermint oil: Synopsis of information|publisher=United States Bureau of Foreign and Domestic Commerce |date=1949|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=4 February 2020}}</ref> Its active ingredients, such as menthol, menthone, and menthyl acetate, give it its minty properties that result in a fresh and cooling sensation when used. Moreover, peppermint is also a good source of vitamin A, vitamin C, magnesium, and potassium.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.encyclopedia.com/plants-and-animals/plants/plants/peppermint |title=Peppermint |date=2020 |publisher=[]Encyclopedia.com]] |url-status=live |archive-url= |archive-date= |access-date=4 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n== History and Extraction ==\nPeppermint and peppermint oil have been used for thousands of years in Ancient Egypt, Greece, and Rome<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.aromafoundry.com/blogs/aroma-foundry/peppermint-oil-uses-description-recipes-precautions|title=Peppermint Oil: Uses, Benefits, & More|last=Santos|first=F.|date=2020|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=4 February 2020}}</ref>. Historical records reveal the use of peppermint in Egyptian tombs and pyramids<ref name=\":1\" />. However, it was not until Carolus Linnaeus catalogued the plant in 1753 that the very first documentation of the plant\u2019s characteristics was written.\n\nPeppermint extract can be obtained through various means, the most common being steam distillation, solvent extraction, and soxhelet extraction<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Siddeeg|first=A.|last2=Mukhtar|first2=R.M.E.|last3=Salih|first3=Z.A.|last4=Ali|first4=A.O.|date=2018|title=Extraction and characterization of peppermint (Mentha piperita) essential oil and its assessment as antioxidant and antibacterial|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/328631741_Extraction_and_Characterization_of_Peppermint_Mentha_piperita_Essential_Oil_and_its_Assessment_as_Antioxidant_and_Antibacterial|journal=|volume=|pages=|via=ResearchGate}}</ref>.\n\n== Uses ==\nPeppermint extract is commonly used as an antiseptic, anti-viral, stimulant, and a flavoring agent<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Tanu|first=B.|last2=Harpreet|first2=K.|date=2016|title=Benefits of essential oil|url=https://mafiadoc.com/benefits-of-essential-oil-journal-of-chemical-and-pharmaceutical_5c174b1f097c47d4198b473d.html|journal=Journal of Chemical and Pharmaceutical Research|volume=8(6)|pages=143-149|via=}}</ref>. Moderate levels of it can be safely mixed into food items, or it can also be applied topically, sprayed on surfaces as a household cleaner, or inhaled using aromatherapy<ref name=\":2\" />.\n\n===Uses in cooking===\n{{unreferenced section|date=February 2015}}\nPeppermint extract can be used to add a peppermint flavor to [[baked goods]], [[desserts]], and [[candy]], particularly [[candy canes]], [[mint (candy)|mints]], and peppermint patties. Extracts for cooking may be labeled as pure, natural, imitation, or artificial. While pure and natural extracts contain peppermint oil specifically, imitation and artificial extracts generally use a mix of ingredients to achieve a flavor resembling peppermint.\n\nPeppermint extract can be substituted in [[recipes]] with peppermint oil (a stronger ingredient primarily used in candy-making), [[cr\u00e8me de menthe]], or [[schnapps|peppermint schnapps]]. If the food is not heated, the alcoholic properties of [[liqueurs]] may remain present in the finished product.\n\nPeppermint extract may also be added to hot water to create [[peppermint tea]].\n\n=== Medicinal uses ===\nMedicinal uses of peppermint extract are well-documented, however the efficacy of most applications is only beginning to be tested in clinical trials.\n\nPeppermint extract is commonly used to soothe symptoms of the [[common cold]] and the [[flu]], and as a [[digestion|digestive]] aid to relieve [[bloating]] and [[flatulence]]. It is an [[anti-inflammatory]] which be used to treat [[arthritis]] and [[rheumatism]].<ref name=\"oils\">{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/completebookofes00worw/page/1|title=The complete book of essential oils and aromatherapy|last=Worwood|first=V.A.|publisher=New World Library|year=1991|isbn=0-931432-82-0|location=|pages=[https://archive.org/details/completebookofes00worw/page/1 1, 20]|url-access=registration}}</ref> It may be used to aid in the relief of pain from [[menstrual cramp]]s and [[headache]]s.<ref name=oils/><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Heshmati|first1=A.|last2=Dolatian|first2=M.|last3=Mojab|first3=F.|last4=Shakeri|first4=N.|last5=Nikkhah|first5=S.|last6=Mahmoodi|first6=Z.|date=2016|year=|title=The effect of peppermint (Mentha piperita) capsules on the severity of primary dysmenorrhea|url=|journal=Journal of Herbal Medicine|volume=6|issue=3|pages=137\u2013141|doi=10.1016/j.hermed.2016.05.001|via=}}</ref> Additionally, peppermint oil may be an effective remedy for [[irritable bowel syndrome]] with constipation.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Ford|first1=A.C.|last2=Talley|first2=N.J.|last3=Spiegel|first3=B.M.R.|last4=Foxx-Orenstein|first4=A.E.|last5=Schiller|first5=L.|last6=Quigley|first6=E.M.M.|last7=Moayyedi|first7=P.|date=|year=2008|title=Effect of fibre, antispasmodics, and peppermint oil in the treatment of irritable bowel syndrome: Systematic review and meta-analysis|url=|journal=BMJ|volume=337|pages=a2313|doi=10.1136/bmj.a2313|pmc=2583392|pmid=19008265|via=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Cappello|first1=G.|last2=Coraggio|first2=D.|last3=De Berardinis|first3=G.|last4=Spezzaferro|first4=M.|last5=Grossi|first5=L.|last6=Marzio|first6=L.|date=|year=2006|title=Peppermint oil (Mintoil\u00ae) in the treatment of irritable bowel syndrome. A prospective double blind placebo controlled randomized trial|url=|journal=Digestive and Liver Disease|volume=38|pages=S202|doi=10.1016/S1590-8658(06)80548-7|via=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Grigoleit|first1=H.|last2=Grigoleit|first2=P.|date=|year=2005|title=Peppermint oil in irritable bowel syndrome|url=|journal=Phytomedicine|volume=12|issue=8|pages=601\u2013606|doi=10.1016/j.phymed.2004.10.005|via=}}</ref> It is also used as a natural remedy for [[toothache]].<ref name=oils/>\n\n===Use as a pest repellent===\nPeppermint oil is commonly used to repel ants, flying insects, rodents, and spiders. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gardenguides.com/81346-use-peppermint-oil-pest-control.html|title=How to use peppermint oil for pest control|last=Douglas|first=E.|date=2017|website=GardenGuides.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n===Use as a physical performance enhancer===\nPeppermint oil is used in endurance sports to improve mental and physical stamina.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Meamarbashi|first1=A.|date=|year=2014|title=Instant effects of peppermint essential oil on the physiological parameters and exercise performance|url=|journal=Avicenna Journal of Phytomedicine|volume=4|issue=1|pages=72\u20138|pmc=4103722|pmid=25050303|via=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Meamarbashi|first1=A.|last2=Rajabi|first2=A.|date=|year=2013|title=The effects of peppermint on exercise performance|url=|journal=Journal of the International Society of Sports Nutrition|volume=10|issue=1|pages=15|doi=10.1186/1550-2783-10-15|pmc=3607906|pmid=23517650|via=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Food additives]]\n", "name_user": "Adrianrorheim", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peppermint_extract"}
{"title_page": "De Primera Mano", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{infobox television |\n  | show_name = De Primera Mano\n  | image = De_primera_mano.png\n  | image_size = 190px\n  | genre = News show\n  | camera = [[Multi-camera setup|Multi-camera]]\n  | runtime = 120 minutes (including commercials)\n  | company = [[Grupo Imagen]]\n  | creator = Laura Flores\n  | presenter = [[Gustavo Adolfo Infante]]<br>[[M\u00f3nica Noguera]]<br>[[Michelle Ruvalcaba]]\n  | location = [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]]<br>(2017-present)\n  | network = [[Imagen Televisi\u00f3n]]\n  | picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])<br>[[480i]] ([[SDTV]])\n  | first_aired = July 24, 2017\n  | last_aired = present\n  | preceded_by = ''No lo cuentes''\n  | followed_by = \n  | num_episodes = \n  | website = http://www.imagentv.com/entretenimiento/de-primera-mano\n  |tv com = \n  }}\n\n'''''De Primera Mano''''' ([[English language|English]]: ''First Hand'') is a [[Mexico|Mexican]] entertainment news show produced and broadcast by [[Imagen Televisi\u00f3n]] since July 24, 2017. The program is characterized by providing information on the latest shows, from which the criticism and opinion of the conductors will be more objective and direct towards the most controversial and shocking of artists in general.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.excelsior.com.mx/funcion/2017/07/24/1177370 |title= M\u00e9xico:'De primera mano' va por todo|access-date=2017-07-24 |archive-url=http://www.excelsior.com.mx/funcion/2017/07/24/1177370|archive-date=2017-07-24 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nIt is broadcast live from the studios of ''Ciudad Imagen'' on Av. Copilco, [[Coyoac\u00e1n]] in [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]], and is hosted by [[Gustavo Adolfo Infante]], [[M\u00f3nica Noguera]] and [[Michelle Ruvalcaba]]. It currently airs Monday through Friday from 15:00 p.m to 17:00 p.m ([[Time in Mexico|UTC]]).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tvnotas.com.mx/noticias-espectaculos-mexico/gustavo-adolfo-infante-tendra-dos-horas-de-primera-mano |title=\u00a1Gustavo Adolfo Infante tendr\u00e1 dos horas \u201cDe primera mano\u201d!|access-date=2019-01-15 |archive-url=https://www.tvnotas.com.mx/noticias-espectaculos-mexico/gustavo-adolfo-infante-tendra-dos-horas-de-primera-mano|archive-date=2017-07-24 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== Promotion ==\n\nFor the promotion of the program, three spots were recorded accompanied by star figures such as the actress [[Itat\u00ed Cantoral]], accompanied by her daughter Maria Itat\u00ed, [[Lis Vega]] and the conductor and actor, [[Ra\u00fal Maga\u00f1a]].\n\n== Presenters ==\n* [[Gustavo Adolfo Infante]] (2017\u2013present) \n* [[M\u00f3nica Noguera]] (2017-present)\n* [[Michelle Ruvalcaba]] (2017\u2013present)\n\n===Former===\n* [[Alexia Almeida]] (2017-18)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.imagentv.com/ Official website at Imagen Televisi\u00f3n]\n\n[[Category:2017 Mexican television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s Mexican television series]]\n[[Category:Imagen Televisi\u00f3n shows]]\n[[Category:Live television series]]\n[[Category:Mexican television news programmes]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language television programs]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{infobox television |\n  | show_name = De Primera Mano\n  | image = De_primera_mano.png\n  | image_size = 190px\n  | genre = News show\n  | camera = [[Multi-camera setup|Multi-camera]]\n  | runtime = 120 minutes (including commercials)\n  | company = [[Grupo Imagen]]\n  | creator = Laura Flores\n  | presenter = [[Gustavo Adolfo Infante]]<br>[[M\u00f3nica Noguera]]<br>[[Michelle Ruvalcaba]]\n  | location = [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]]<br>(2017-present)\n  | network = [[Imagen Televisi\u00f3n]]\n  | picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])<br>[[480i]] ([[SDTV]])\n  | first_aired = July 24, 2017\n  | last_aired = present\n  | preceded_by = ''No lo cuentes''\n  | followed_by = \n  | num_episodes = \n  | website = http://www.imagentv.com/entretenimiento/de-primera-mano\n  |tv com = \n  }}\n\n'''''De Primera Mano''''' ([[English language|English]]: ''First Hand'') is a [[Mexican]] entertainment news show produced and broadcast by [[Imagen Televisi\u00f3n]] since July 24, 2017. The program is characterized by providing information on the latest shows, from which the criticism and opinion of the conductors will be more objective and direct towards the most controversial and shocking of artists in general.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.excelsior.com.mx/funcion/2017/07/24/1177370 |title= M\u00e9xico:'De primera mano' va por todo|access-date=2017-07-24 |archive-url=http://www.excelsior.com.mx/funcion/2017/07/24/1177370|archive-date=2017-07-24 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nIt is broadcast live from the studios of ''Ciudad Imagen'' on Av. Copilco, [[Coyoac\u00e1n]] in [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]], and is hosted by [[Gustavo Adolfo Infante]], [[M\u00f3nica Noguera]] and [[Michelle Ruvalcaba]]. It currently airs Monday through Friday from 15:00 p.m to 17:00 p.m ([[Time in Mexico|UTC]]).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tvnotas.com.mx/noticias-espectaculos-mexico/gustavo-adolfo-infante-tendra-dos-horas-de-primera-mano |title=\u00a1Gustavo Adolfo Infante tendr\u00e1 dos horas \u201cDe primera mano\u201d!|access-date=2019-01-15 |archive-url=https://www.tvnotas.com.mx/noticias-espectaculos-mexico/gustavo-adolfo-infante-tendra-dos-horas-de-primera-mano|archive-date=2017-07-24 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== Promotion ==\n\nFor the promotion of the program, three spots were recorded accompanied by star figures such as the actress [[Itat\u00ed Cantoral]], accompanied by her daughter Maria Itat\u00ed, [[Lis Vega]] and the conductor and actor, [[Ra\u00fal Maga\u00f1a]].\n\n== Presenters ==\n* [[Gustavo Adolfo Infante]] (2017\u2013present) \n* [[M\u00f3nica Noguera]] (2017-present)\n* [[Michelle Ruvalcaba]] (2017\u2013present)\n\n===Former===\n* [[Alexia Almeida]] (2017-18)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.imagentv.com/ Official website at Imagen Televisi\u00f3n]\n\n[[Category:2017 Mexican television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s Mexican television series]]\n[[Category:Imagen Televisi\u00f3n shows]]\n[[Category:Live television series]]\n[[Category:Mexican television news programmes]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language television programs]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toMexican(link changed toMexico) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/De_Primera_Mano"}
{"title_page": "Sale El Sol (TV program)", "text_new": "{{short description|Mexican television morning show}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Sale El Sol\n| image                    = Logotipook.png\n| image_size               = 150px\n| genre                    = [[Breakfast television|Morning news/talk]]<br>[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]]\n| creator                  = \n| director                 = \n| presenter                = [[Luz Mar\u00eda Zetina]]<br>Carlos Arenas<br>Paulina Mercado<br>Roberto Carlo<br>\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \"Sale el Sol\" by N\u00e9bulas\n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = Mexico\n| language                 = Spanish\n| num_seasons              = 4\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = \n| producer                 = Andr\u00e9s Tovar<br>(2016-present)<br>Natalia Pereda Fern\u00e1ndez<br>(2019-present)<br>David Ortiz Marquet<br>(2017-2019)<br>Eric Reid<br>(2016-2017)\n| location                 = [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]]<br>(2016-present)\n| editor                   = \n| camera                   = [[Multi-camera setup|Multi-camera]]\n| runtime                  = 180 minutes (including commercials)\n| company                  = [[Grupo Imagen]]\n| distributor              = \n| network                  = [[Imagen Televisi\u00f3n]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])<br>[[480i]] ([[SDTV]])\n| first_aired              = October 18, 2016\n| last_aired               = present\n| preceded_by              = ''Nuestro D\u00eda''\n| followed_by              = \n| related                  = \n| website                  = http://www.imagentv.com/entretenimiento/sale-el-sol\n| production_website       = \n}}\n\n'''''Sale El Sol''''' ([[English language|English]]: ''The Sun Comes Out'') is a [[Mexico|Mexican]] [[breakfast television|television daily morning program]] produced by Andr\u00e9s Tovar for [[Imagen Televisi\u00f3n]]. The program is intended for the general public and includes various sections and topics of interest related to beauty, cooking, entertainment, horoscopes, sexuality, tips, reflections, promotions, interviews, shows and music. It is one of the first programs broadcast by the new [[Grupo Imagen]]'s television network, launched on October 17, 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.prensario.net/17825-Mexico-Imagen-TV-anuncio-la-programacion-para-el-estreno-del-17-de-octubre.note.aspx |title= M\u00e9xico: Imagen TV anunci\u00f3 la programaci\u00f3n para el estreno del 17 de octubre |access-date=2016-10-07 |archive-url= https://www.prensario.net/17825-Mexico-Imagen-TV-anuncio-la-programacion-para-el-estreno-del-17-de-octubre.note.aspx |archive-date=2016-03-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nIt is broadcast live from the studios of ''Ciudad Imagen'' on Av. Copilco, [[Coyoac\u00e1n]] in [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]], and is hosted by [[Luz Mar\u00eda Zetina]], Carlos Arenas, Paulina Mercado and Roberto Carlo. It premiered on October 18, 2016, and currently airs Monday through Friday from 9:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m ([[Time in Mexico|UTC]]).\n\n==On-air staff==\n===Curent===\n====Presenters====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name !! Debut\n|-\n|[[Luz Mar\u00eda Zetina]] ||(2016\u2013present) \n|-\n|Carlos Arenas || (2016-present)\n|-\n|Paulina Mercado || (2016\u2013present)\n|-\n|Roberto Carlo || (2017\u2013present)\n|-\n|}\n\n====Contributors====\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n'''Entertainment'''\n* Gustavo Adolfo Infante (2016\u2013present)\n* [[Ana Mar\u00eda Alvarado]] (2016\u2013present)\n* Hector Vargas (2016\u2013present)\n* Joanna Vega-Briesto (2018\u2013present)\n* Manolo Carmona (2018\u2013present)\n'''Specialists'''\n* Pepe Bandera (2016\u2013present)\n* Julie Salom\u00f3n (2016\u2013present)\n* Rox Armendariz (2017\u2013present)\n* Od\u00edn Dupeyr\u00f3n (2017\u2013present)\n* Daniel Habif (2018\u2013pres